Sentencas: The performance of Ni/SrO-doped CeO2 (SrDC) anode-supported cells, combined with the Sm2O3-doped CeO2 (SDC) electrolyte layer, has been investigated for the direct supply of a thy CH4.
Titulo: SrO Doping Effect on Fabrication and Performance of Ni/Ce1-xSrxO2-x Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell for Direct Methane Utilization

Sentencas: The SrO content in the Ce1-xSrxO2-x solid solution affects the porous structure of the starting anode support comprising of the sintered NiO and Ce1-xSrxO2-x grains and denseness of the SDC layer by co-sintering.
Titulo: SrO Doping Effect on Fabrication and Performance of Ni/Ce1-xSrxO2-x Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell for Direct Methane Utilization

Sentencas: The cell using the 5 mol% SrO-doped CeO2 shows the highest cell performance without time-dependent degradation even at 750 degrees C.
Titulo: SrO Doping Effect on Fabrication and Performance of Ni/Ce1-xSrxO2-x Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell for Direct Methane Utilization

Sentencas: This cell (the 5SrDC cell) also provides better cell performance with decreasing operating temperature than the conventional Ni/YSZ anode-supported cell (the YSZ cell); the maximum power density of the 5SrDC cell is higher than that of the YSZ cell by 73% at 650 degrees C.
Titulo: SrO Doping Effect on Fabrication and Performance of Ni/Ce1-xSrxO2-x Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell for Direct Methane Utilization

Sentencas: This enhancement effect is discussed in light of the mixed ionic-electronic conduction of the CeO2-based solid electrolytes.
Titulo: SrO Doping Effect on Fabrication and Performance of Ni/Ce1-xSrxO2-x Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell for Direct Methane Utilization
